{"by":"anovikov","id":47776549,"parent":47776366,"text":"Successful products are usually built from inside the system, not from outside - and then it doesn&#x27;t matter if 50 people from the outside copied it, they won&#x27;t get paid because they aren&#x27;t the right people to begin with.<p>Now problem is, because people from outside usually don&#x27;t know it, and believe they are relevant, they used to create the vast majority of &quot;investment&quot; demand for coding... and now because they ask themselves the same question as you did, they just stopped trying, and their demand is gone.","time":1776244223,"type":"comment"}